Description: inswinging low full toss. Kept out by Brook. Surprised a touch by the length
shape back in again. Even from short of a length. Brook opens the face and takes a single
on a length, tight line again, some shape, 127ks. Clipped away for one
Brook is disdainful now. Gives him some width, and Brook dances down the track to drive Tendulkar over extra cover
looks like a slower one. Bowled at 123ks. On a length, Brook opens the face to short third
well bowled. Brook is making room, and he follows him with a slower bouncer at 107ks. Brook manages to cut it down but straight to point
on target, top of off. Defended
Agarwal is looking to advance, Behrendorff goes shorter and follows him. The mis-hit gets him a single to mid-on
sumptuous. Push-drive on the up. Threads the needle between cover-point and cover. Replay this a hundred times
short ball, cramps him up, and draws the top edge. This is not a slower edge, and it is at his shoulder. Brook is surprised by it. Looking to hit it still, and the edge settles at cover-point
short of a length, outside off, runs this down to deep third for one
cut away to deep third for one
Agarwal backs away, Meredith follows him with a length, and he punches it down the ground. Gets superb timiing on it. Beats long-on
gets inside the line to work this to deep square
keeps the pull down for a single to deep square leg
slower ball as Agarwal backs away again. Just the single to long-on
he has smacked this pull. Short again, but this time outside off, Stands tall and goes over midwicket. Right out of the screws
on a length, just outside off, pushed to cover
wide legbreak, skips down the wicket, drives to deep cover
legbreak, outside off, punched to deep cover for one
short of a length, goes back to pull this to deep midwicket
superb shot. Flighted outside off, and drills this wide of long-off for four. All along the ground
looks for a slog into the leg side, but is beaten on the inside edge. Headed down leg, though
slows this one down, Agarwal runs it behind square but straight to short third. With that, the required rate goes pasttwo a ball
hits him high on the bat with a length ball, but he has managed to place it between square leg and long leg for a couple
shows him the ramp early, Green goes for the slower ball, but he is good enough to delay the shot and manages to clear short fine
slower short ball, pulled to long leg for one

big appeal for lbw on the yorker, not given, and they have reviewed it. Agarwal has shuffled across, but the umpire reckons it is sliding down. First replay suggests he might be right. Beaten on the inside edge but it is missing leg. MI lose both their reviews
yorker again. Swinging in. Is it reversing? Dug out for a single
misses the yorker by inches, but goes only for a single to deep midwicket as Agarwal is hit on the inside half of the bat. I could be wrong, but I suspect it might be reversing
Chawla follows him as he comes down the track and looks to make room. There is no pace to work with. He lofts it to deep square leg for one
legbreak. Some turn too. And Klaasen is down for a reverse early. Gets a toe end. Looking to go over short third but ends up going over point
the biggest six of the night. Flat, quick, and right in the slot. Looks like a seam-up delivery. Klaasen has bludgeoned it over Chawla's head for a huge six
and now a reverse-swept six. Again shows it early, again ends up going squarer than he wants but he has timed this well. Middled it
looks to defend with a flat shortish delivery but Klaasen picks the length early and manufactures a pull here. And he ends up going wide of deep midwicket

he looks to hit a six off the back foot. It is a wrong'un, which he has read here, but again it comes slowly off the surface and takes the toe end of the bat. David runs to his left and forward from long-on to take a well-judged overhead catch
yorker again, and right on the money. Dug out back to him
another yorker on the money. Dug out for a single. There is some tail here
on a length now. Punched to deep cover for one
yorker, and follows him as he backs away. Just the single to deep square leg

another catch for David. Meredith misses the yorker, but the low full toss is good enough, especially when it follows Agarwal and takes his arms away from him. He can manage to send it to long-on for an overhead catch, which David smartly takes
beaten on the inside edge. Seams in off a length, and beats the inside edge. Kishan dives to his left and gets a hand to it
spot on with the yorker, Jansen squeezes it out for one to point
another yorker. Perhaps slightly fuller than one. It tails away this time to beat his outside edge
outswing. remarkable bowling. I think it is reversing, and he is playing with the shiny side.Yes definite reverse. Beats the outside edge. The shiny side on the outside
looks for the yorker, short by a few inches. Pushed to extra cover for one
misses the yorker, and Jansen gets low to hit this half-volley straight of long-off for four
yorker, spot on, but Jansen gets the outside half of the toe end on this, and it squeezes past short third for four lucky runs
swing and a miss as Meredith comes back
nails the yorker. On leg. Dug out for one
lovely shot. He has missed the yorker only by inches, and he drives it back above his head with a high elbow for the pose. Bisects long-off and long-on
another catch for David. Meredith sees the yorker has a small margin for error, and goes short and slow. Jansen has no choice but to go four a boundary every ball. Ends up skying it to long-on
and now he is back to the yorker. Dot ball as he digs it out back to the bowler
slower ball, completely done in, but the miscue lands well short of long-off
yorker gone wrong. Nice knee-high full toss, and he chips it over extra cover for four
goes to good length, driven to deep cover for one
yorker, on off stump, dug out for a single to long-off
slower ball, on a length, but gives him the width, which allows Washington to open the face and beat short third

lazy running. Two yorkers in one ball. Behrendorff bowls one, and Washington digs it out for what looks like a comfortable single to mid-off. David lets a throw rip, catches the stumps on the yorker, and Washington is casual. Not even stretching his arm fully let alone diving
how many half-edges will go past short third tonight? Behrnedorff bowls well enough, gets an outside edge on this near yorker, but the third is inside the circle. anything past him is four
inswing, on a length, top of off. Opens the face for. single
oh Green is lucky. He is sliding down leg, and is lucky there is no bat on this because fine leg is up. One leg-bye only
nails the yorker. Follows him too as he backs away. Dug out back to him
goes short as expected, runs this down to deep third for one
still reversing. Beats the inside edge on the slog. Half a shout for lbw but this is sliding down
reversing yorker. On leg stump. Dug out into nthe stumps at the non-striker's. Samad doesn't take the single off the ricochet. He wants the strike
looks for the yorker, gets in a low full toss outside off. Samad gets a nick on it, but Kishan saves four with a dive to his right
wide yorker again, toe-ended to deep point, and he runs himself out taking a non-existent second
yorker, on off, played with an open face to deep point
he shuffles across looking to sweep but Tendulkar stays with the yorker. Hits his back pad for a leg-bye
first wicket for Tendulkar in the IPL. SRH bowled out. Misses the yorker by inches, Bhuvneshwar tries to go down the ground, but gets an outside edge to extra cover. What a moment for Tendulkar jr.
smartly bowled. Sees Agarwal make room, and slips one in wide outside off
now he denies him any room with one short of a length. Another dot
pulled away to deep square for one
short of a length, on off, run down to short third for one
on a length, on the pads, dragged to deep square leg for one
nicely played. Tendulkar goes short of a length, doesn't give him much room, but Tripathi opens the face and guides this between short third and point. Gets four
on a length, on the pads, worked to leg for a single
on a length, stump to stump, Tripathi drops and runs for a single
pushed wide of mid-on for another single
Behrendorff is on fire. On target, just around off, and on a length. Tripathi is looking to run it down because the big shot is not on. The angle takes the edge, and MI have two early wickets
on a length, on off, defended from the crease
short of a length, tucked away off the hip for one
on a length, angling in, hits the thigh pad as he looks to work this away to leg
full and straight, punched to mid-on
on a length, punched to mid-off, and they take on the tall left-arm seamer Behrendorff for a quick single
shades of the Agarwal of old. Slower ball, picks it, and plays half-sweep-half-pickup over square leg for a six
back to top of off. Defended
backs away. Meredith follows him. Manages to swipe it over the infield, comes back for two
on a length, punched straight of mid-off for one
cleverly played. On a length, gets some width, and opens the face to guide it between short third nad backward point for four
full and straight now, clipped straight to midwicket
looks to go over mid-off, gets a thick edge to deep cover
looks like a cutter, 133ks, short of a length, beats him attempt to go over mid-off
on a length, on leg, worked to square leg for another single
and there is immediate turn for him. Cramps him up, but they squeeze in a single
on a length, outside off, no turn, pushed back to him
slower in the air, still not a half-volley, uses soft hands to work this into a gap on the leg side for a couple
punched to deep midwicket for one. Shokeen stays out of the driving arc without bowling too short
Shokeen is not giving them anything to hit so Markram dances down the wicket to create one. Lofts him over midwicket for a clean six. Just the right space between him and the pitch of the ball
gets the shorter ball now, and cuts it to deep cover for two
on a length, legreak, pushed to long-on for one
wider on the crease, looks like a slider, flatter in the air. Pushed down to long-on again
Agarwal down the wicket, gets close to its pitch, and lofts him back over his head for four
slider again, quicker one, pulled to deep square leg
goes back to punch this wide of long-on, and they steal the second again
Sharma might just have saved three there. Chawla goes flat and short, he cuts it in front of square, and a big dive from Sharma keeps them to one
starts off with a short ball that doesn't get big on him. Pulled through square leg for four
on a length, wicket to wicket, swiped to deep square leg for one
on a length, on top of off, runs this down to deep third for a single

Green is turning everything to gold. Markram clears the front leg and slogs, but I suspect it is the slowness off the surface that draws the miscue. Toe-ended to deep midwicket. Huge wicket in this SRH line-up
on a length, wicket to wicket, pushed to mid-on for one
wicket to wicket, on a length, pushed to short midwicket

seems to have picked the wrong'un but still doesn't get enough power in the shot. He is possibly looking to go over cover, but the googly doesn't turn that much, and takes the inner half of the bat for a simple catch to long-off
wide on the crease, pushes one through, punched to deep cover
legbreak, full, middle and leg, worked to deep square
another legbreak. This one turns too. Defended in front of off
pushes this through, Klaasen hits it down to long-off for one
wrong'un, punched to deep midwicket for another single
